# 📺 Netflix Data Analysis with Python & Pandas

This project explores and analyzes Netflix’s dataset to extract insights on content trends using Python, Pandas, and Matplotlib.

---

## 📁 Dataset
- Source: [Netflix Dataset – Kaggle](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/shivamb/netflix-shows)
- Records: 7,000+
- Columns: Title, Director, Country, Date Added, Genre, etc.

---

## 🧼 Data Cleaning
- Handled missing values in `country` and `director` columns
- Converted `date_added` column to datetime format
- Extracted `year_added` for time-based analysis

---

## 🔍 Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
- 📊 Year-wise content addition
- 🌍 Top 10 countries with most Netflix content
- 🎭 Most common genres on the platform
- 📈 Content type distribution (Movies vs TV Shows)

